<br>
For fletching, visit <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://members.bellatlantic.net/%7Eewj/fletchguide/raising_skill.htm">this</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> guide.  It's old, but still valid &amp; is the best guide to raising fletching.  Make regular arrows up to 202 (I went with field, wood, small, ceramic for the last 20 points, IIRC), then, depending on how much plat you have, farm ingredients for Acrylia arrows or make Darkwood bows (only if you have money to throw away).<br>
<br>
Good luck; it's a hard route, but can be rewarding once you reach the top.<br>
<br>
BTW; for pottery, don't ever fire your combines in the kiln unless it's an item you want to keep or sell.  Firing has a lower trivial level than creating the item to begin with, and just costs you more money. <p>Sionach An'Talamh, Retired Outrider</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sionach>Sionach</A> at: 1/14/03 7:15:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordmaldian>LordMaldian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://userpages.prexar.com/marsroy/Brenda/deathav.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(1/14/03 9:07:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=468.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dragoon.com.au/clipart/iconsgothic/demonred.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Posting for help....</span><hr size=1> Thanks Sionach. I will be looking for you in case I have a question or two. Useful information and I will be able to move up in the tradeskills now. Appreciate it! <p><body>

